## {{ offering.display_name | default("Ollama Model") }}

This service provides the {{ offering.display_name | default("Ollama") }} model through UnitySVC.
{% if has_managed %}

## Managed

Use the `managed` channel to route requests to Ollama Cloud with the seller-managed
API key. No customer Ollama API key is required for this channel.
{% endif %}
{% if has_byok %}

## BYOK

Use the `byok` channel to route requests to Ollama Cloud with your own Ollama API
key. Store your key as `OLLAMA_API_KEY` in your customer secrets before using this
channel.
{% endif %}

## BYOE

Use the `byoe` channel to route requests to your own Ollama-compatible endpoint.

1. Install Ollama on your machine or server: [ollama.com/download](https://ollama.com/download)
2. Pull the model: `ollama pull {{ model_name }}`
3. Expose your Ollama server through a public DNS name or public IP address that
   the UnitySVC gateway can reach
4. Configure firewall rules, port forwarding, reverse proxy, and TLS as needed
   so the platform can connect to that endpoint
5. Provide the public base URL during enrollment, such as
   `https://ollama.example.com`

## Best Practices

1. Pull the required model before using the service.
2. Monitor GPU, CPU, and memory usage on your Ollama server.
3. Use HTTPS and authentication when exposing Ollama over the internet.
{% if has_managed or has_byok %}4. Use exponential backoff for Ollama Cloud rate limits.
5. Never expose Ollama API keys in client-side code.
{% endif %}
